$ Python functions

{ Global/local variables in a function

  A → development/languages/Python/variables[variable] that is only referenced in a → development/languages/Python/functions[function], but not assigned to, is implicitely a global variable.

  In order to make explicitely mark a variable in a function as global, the → development/languages/Python/statements/global[`global` statement] must be used.

